text: good stuff, i like the arpeggiator one

Hello

I wanted to announce a brownbag lunch talk from Steve Lee. He will be coming in tomorrow, to talk about some insights from his years of ethnographic research, focusing on changing systems and service design. Steve also might share his recent work on homelessness, and social innovation.

Steve is from the UK and used to work at Ziba for a while. He has gone back in the UK but currently visiting Portland.

I’d like to encourage everyone to attend, Steve is a pretty interesting person, working on amazing things.

His website is: <http://steveleedesign.net/>
Bring your lunch and listen (3rd floor kitchen) invite to come …
(Marce just posted a similar thing on ‘general’)
